reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Used as a vanity
reviews.reviewText: So far so good. I bought this for my daughter to use as a vanity. After seeing vanities with not many reviews and not good reviews at that I was in doubt getting one for my daughter. Add on the higher cost, most seemed to have some quality issues, and maybe even paying for shipping as most were say $30-75 to ship, and the hassle of maybe having damage and a return etc. I just couldn't do it. She was agreeable at looking for desks and this was her choice and she is happy with it. It has a lot of room for a LED mirror, make up organizers, medium size blue tooth speakers, and also has some drawers. It was easy to assemble alone, and I think it took me an hour to an hour and a half, but I take my time with picture instructions. Someone could probably easily do it in 30 minutes with help, but i like to do things alone and slowly. Everything came labeled, no damage, and arrived quickly. It will get her through high school as a desk and vanity and for the price that is long enough, though it may last longer, and I am happy with the purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I needed an L-Shaped desk for my laptop and 2 monitors with space for my note pad and a printer. A filing cabinet and drawers for usual desk necessities was a must. I was nervous at first because there were virtually no reviews for this product but Tribesigns had thousands of great reviews, they did not disappoint. There was only one flaw, an arm on the drawer/file piece was not soldered on one side but it's not weight bearing, I'm not worried about it. This is a fantastic desk for a low price. I even did a simple dismantle to make it easier for our move. It's lightweight yet strong. Love this desk.
